  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14843">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Discuss the importance of the Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the
      Outdoor Code as they relate to Mammal Study. Explain how you have followed
      the Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code while in natural
      areas during field observation, specimen collection, and identification.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a
        href="https://vimeo.com/1115216743/63b20c0b33?share=copy"
        target="_blank"
        >Leave No Trace Basics (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/jXO1uY0MvmQ" target="_blank"
        >Leave No Trace Outdoor Ethics (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14844">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14844 mb-requirement-id-14845">
        (a) Explore careers related to this merit badge. Research one career to
        learn about the training and education needed, costs, job prospects,
        salary, job duties, and career advancement. Your research methods may
        include—with your parent or guardian's permission—an internet or library
        search, an interview with a professional in the field, or a visit to a
        location where people in this career work. Discuss with your counselor
        both your findings and what about this profession might make it an
        interesting career. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/AK2Onqx-ctM?si=LwrbzHPsoZ0MrkDp"
          target="_blank"
          >10+ Wildlife Biology Careers You Should Know About (&amp; Salaries)
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14844 mb-requirement-id-14846">
        (b) Explore how you could use knowledge and skills from this merit badge
        to pursue a hobby or healthy lifestyle. Research any training needed,
        expenses, and organizations that promote or support it. Discuss with
        your counselor what short-term and long-term goals you might have if you
        pursued this. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C4HjfzY3z90" target="_blank"
          >Top Tips to get into Wildlife Photography (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/kgtt21yKZOw?si=f5yRyDVQYFQXD4YB"
          target="_blank"
          >A Look Inside the Life of a Wildlife Rehab Volunteer (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
